%N A084159 Pell oblongs.
%C A084159 Essentially the same as A046727.
%C A084159 Consider the finite continued fraction 2 + 1/(2 + 1/(2 + ...)) with 2*n 2's, but the middle numerator is -1 instead of 1. This continued fraction is equal to a(n)/(2*P(n)^2) for P(n) = A000129(n), the n-th Pell number. For example, when n=2, our continued fraction would be 2 + 1/(2 + (-1)/(2 + 1/2)) = 21/8, which is a(2)/(2*P(2)^2). - _Greg Dresden_ and Jiaqian Zhang, Sep 11 2025
%D A084159 Albert H. Beiler, Recreations in the theory of numbers, New York, Dover, (2nd ed.) 1966. See Table 60 at p. 123.
